    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation (what does it say?) to the author's intent in his canonical and historical context. Psalm 24 is a liturgical poem of three distinct movements, each built on a rhetorical question and its answer. The movements below follow the psalm's own argument: creation theology grounds ethics; ethics qualify the worshiper for encounter; encounter reveals the identity of the One who was always coming. Where the Hebrew sharpens meaning beyond what English conveys, a note follows as supplement.",
